It takes effort to run a somewhat unexpected campaign. First, Świtalski has to be convinced to run. He himself doesn't expect he has a chance against well known Daszyński, and it takes a good deal of prodding to convince him of his destiny.

Some minority MPs will likely support us. Who else will? Can we convince other parties to support him as well?

