view-if: bbwr_speaker_campaign > 0 and pps_support_bbwr == 0 
max-visits: 1

The KPP is committed to supporting Ernst Thälmann. [? if pps_relation >= 45 : However, the Nazi-Hindenburg coalition worries them enough that they are willing to be convinced to drop their campaign and support Braun. ?][? if pps_relation < 45 : They do not seem willing to be convinced. ?]

- @r2_pps_resources: Use our resources.
- @r2_pps_relations: Use our good relations.
- @round2_menu: Forget about the KPP.

@r2_pps_resources
view-if: pps_relation >= 45 and not historical_mode
choose-if: resources >= 3
subtitle: -3 resources
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources (need 3).
on-arrival: resources -= 3; pps_support_bbwr = 1
go-to: round2_menu

The KPP now endorses Braun in the presidential election! We ask them to keep their support low-key, so as to not alienate the bourgeois voters.

@r2_pps_relations
view-if: pps_relation >= 60
unavailable-subtitle: Our relations are not good enough.
on-arrival: pps_support_bbwr = 1
go-to: round2_menu

The KPP now endorses Braun in the presidential election! We ask them to keep their support low-key, so as to not alienate the bourgeois voters. 

@round2_thalmann
view-if: bbwr_support_daszynski == 0 and pps_support_bbwr == 0
choose-if: pps_relation >= 50 and repairers_strength > colonels_strength 
unavailable-subtitle: [? if pps_relation < 50 : We do not have good enough relations with the Communists, so they are not even willing to accept our support. ?] [? if colonels_strength >= repairers_strength : The reformist faction is able to dissuade the party from supporting this bizarre arrangement. ?]
max-visits: 1

Supporting Thälmann is rather unpopular in our party, even if the Communists accept our support. Are we sure?

- @round2_thalmann_2: Yes, we will support Thälmann, despite the reformists' pleas against it.
- @round2_menu: Never mind.

@round2_thalmann_2
on-arrival: bbwr_speaker_campaign = 0; bbwr_support_daszynski = 1; colonels_dissent += 15; liberals_dissent += 10; sanacja_left_dissent += 5; conservatives_dissent += 10; mniejszosci_bbwr -= 5; robotnicy_bbwr -= 3; pps_relation += 10; pps_bbwr_coalition += 2; pschd_relation -= 15; pslp_relation -= 15
on-departure: pps_support_bbwr = 0; pps_support_bbwr = 0;

Fine. We have thrown our support to Chairman Thälmann of the KPP.

[? if pps_support_bbwr : The Center Party is confused at our capricious behavior, and have switched their support to Hindenburg. ?]

- @round2_vote: Let the second round voting begin.

@round2_hindenburg
view-if: bbwr_speaker_campaign > 0 or bbwr_support_daszynski > 0
on-arrival: bbwr_speaker_campaign = 0; bbwr_support_daszynski = 0

We have switched our support to Hindenburg.

- @round2_vote: Let the second round voting begin.

@round2_vote
go-to: election_algorithm
set-jump: post_election

@round2_results
go-to: bbwr_speaker_wins if bbwr_speaker_plurality == 1; pps_speaker_wins if pps_plurality == 1; sn_speaker_wins if sn_plurality == 1


@bbwr_speaker_wins
on-arrival: speaker = [+ bbwr_candidate +]; speaker_party = "BBWR"; colonels_dissent -= 15; liberals_dissent -= 15; sanacja_left_dissent -= 15; repairers_dissent -= 5; robotnicy_bbwr += 8*(1-dissent); klasa_wyzsza_bbwr += 5*(1-dissent); klasa_srednia_bbwr += 5*(1-dissent); chlopi_bbwr += 5*(1-dissent); bezrobotni_bbwr += 5*(1-dissent);

[+ bbwr_candidate +] of the BBWR has won the Speaker election! This is a moment of celebration for our party, and his victory is able to bolster our support.

@pps_speaker_wins
on-arrival: speaker = [+ pps_candidate +]; speaker_party = "PPS";

Ernst Thälmann of the KPP has won the presidency. Immediately, the far-right launches a coup attempt against the government. We have no choice but to unite with the KPP against the fascists...

- @civil_war: This is civil war.

@sn_speaker_wins
on-arrival: speaker = [+ sn_candidate +]; speaker_party = "ZLN"

[+ sn_candidate +], ZLN candidate has won the Speaker election.

- @hitler_takes_power: What do we do now?


